echo $0 --> to check shell started by the terminal
cat /etc/shells  --> to check available shells in the system

Note: To make shell script, make a file with .sh extension.It should contains linux commands that will run when script is run.
Make script executable using chmod then run it e.g. ./script_file

Add #!/bin/bash for the shebang 
Use `#` to precede a comment

To make make configurations to vim persistent, add to ~/.vimrc.
To make make configurations to bash persistent, add to ~/.bashrc.


